Class ControllerOpponent

  • java.lang.Object
    • Controllers.ControllerOpponent

  • public class ControllerOpponent
extends java.lang.Object
    The class ControllerOpponent is used to create a game. It will display all online users and give the user the opportunity to challenge a player.

      • findOpponent

        public void findOpponent(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        The method finds a user to challenge. It will check if the user is you or if the user is online. If the user is not you and is online, a game will be created by using makeGame. The user will then be sent to a Wait scene.
        Parameters:
        event - is a necessary parameter which is used in a method from the class ChangeScene.

      • checkOpponent

        public int checkOpponent(java.lang.String opponentName)
        The method finds a user to challenge. It will check if the user is you or if the user is online. If the user is not you and is online, a game will be created by using makeGame.
        Parameters:
        opponentName - is the opponent's username
        Returns:
        an int which represents if the opponent is you, is online or does not exist.
